   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    The sign for "mad"
    <font face="Arial">
     (as in the opposite of 
	happy) uses a single motion. If you use a double motion and a slightly less 
	intense face it can mean, "grouchy" or "grumpy."
    </font>
    Don't
    <font face="Arial">
     actually touch your face while doing this sign.  (That might be painful, and 
	then you'd be
     <i>
      really
     </i>
     "mad" at me.)
     <br/>
    </font>
   </p>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    MAD:
   </p>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    <img border="0" height="237" src="/images/madc1.jpg" width="227"/>
    <img border="0" height="237" src="/images/madc2.jpg" width="227"/>
    <img border="0" height="237" src="/images/madc3.jpg" width="227"/>
   </p>
